Enforce immediate settlement of outstanding cash advances totaling ₱13,643,969.85 pursuant to COA Circular Nos. 97-02 and COA Circular No. 2012-004 dated February 10, 1997 and November 28, 2012, respectively;

Prioritize issuance of demand letters to all accountable officers who are in active service;
Impose the withholding of salary and the institution of other sanctions as provided under paragraphs 9.2 and 9.3 of COA Circular 97-002 dated February 10, 1997;

Ensure that no additional cash advances be granted to those officials and employees with unliquidated cash advances pursuant to the provisions of Section 89 of PD No.1445 and Item 5.1.3 of COA Circular No. 97-002 dated February 10, 1997;

Require retiring accountable official or employee to undertake an authorization (in affidavit form) to deduct financial obligations including unliquidated cash advances from the terminal leave benefits pursuant to 5.1.3 of COA Circular No. 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012; and



Assign personnel from the Accounting Office who will closely monitor the movement of the long outstanding cash advances and to prepare quarterly report copy furnished the Audit Team.

