Recommendation:
We recommended that the City Mayor and the City Accountant:
Require the AOs to liquidate their outstanding cash advances, through submission of the necessary supporting documents and refund the unexpended balance, if any;
Immediately send demand letters to officials and employees who have long outstanding cash advances to settle the overdue amounts within a specific period. Otherwise, effect the withholding of their salaries pursuant to Item 5.1.3 of COA Circular No. 97-002 until such time that the cash advances are fully settled;
Strictly require officials and employees to liquidate their cash advances within the prescribed period pursuant to Item 5.1 of COA Circular No. 97-002 dated February 10, 1997; and
File request for authority to write-off dormant or long outstanding unliquidated cash advances, if necessary, to the Office of the Auditor pursuant to COA Circular No. 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016.

Recommendation:
We recommended that the City Accountant:
Record the Financial Assistance to the DepEd or the Silay Schools Division as Due from National Government Agencies (NGAs) pursuant to the Revised Chart of Accounts for LGUs;
Require the liquidation of fund transfer/financial assistance so that the expense accounts are accordingly recognized in the books of the City and a copy of the Official Receipt (OR) for the refund of the unexpended/unutilized balance of funds transferred, if any;
Require that the Memorandum of Agreement (MOA) be attached as supporting document for every fund transfer or financial assistance released to the DEPED pursuant to Item 3.1.1 of COA Circular No. 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012.
